Another step, and Cody reached the opening, Lulu trailing behind. The corridor was dark, as he had come to expect, and
appeared to head off to the left. Cody considered a moment, then took the loop on his end of the leash and slid it around
his wrist, leaving his hand free. He took hold of the haft of the pole sickle with that same hand, so he now had both hands
on the polearm. “Better,” he said. “As long as Lulu doesn't try to run off at the wrong time.”
